			Kirkland Represents HGGC in Formation of $1.33 Billion Fund II
		
Kirkland & Ellis represented HGGC, a leading middle-market private
equity investment firm, which last week announced that it completed
fundraising for HGGC Fund II, L.P. with total capital commitments of
approximately $1.33 billion.

The Kirkland team that represented HGGC is led by private funds partners
Sarah Kirson and Justin Solomon, and includes private funds associates Sojeong
Hong, Lily Rasel and Steve Yoo, tax partner Donald Rocap and associate Joel
Peters-Fransen, investment management partners Scott Moehrke and Kevin
Bettsteller, European regulatory partner Lisa Cawley and associate Prem Mohan,
and employee benefits partner Laura Bader, of counsel LeighAnne Thompson and
associate Jake Glazeski.
The Private Funds Practice at Kirkland & Ellis is one of the largest
and most experienced sponsor-side practices in the world. Since 1995,
Kirkland's private funds lawyers have represented approximately 400 unique
private equity sponsors in more than 770 total funds, raising nearly $510
billion.








